a\ncollection, as the number of nodes increases. For the special case of linear\ndynamics, a separation principle is constructed wherein the optimal estimate is\ncomputed by a Kalman-like filter, irrespective of the probability distribution\nof random variables...\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Dec 2019 11:07:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Dec 2019 22:02:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 14 Dec 2019 19:18:10 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 24 Jan 2020 05:59:21 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 10 Apr 2020 02:53:38 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 2 Jun 2020 11:51:25 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Mon, 29 Mar 2021 14:54:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-30"}
